---
import SectionInner from "../atoms/SectionInner.astro";
---

<section class="px-8 py-28 max-lg:py-20 max-sm:px-5 relative bg-mk-warm">
  <SectionInner>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-[1.2fr_0.8fr] gap-16 items-start max-lg:grid-cols-1 max-lg:gap-8">
      <div class="animate-mk-fade-in-up duration-[800ms] delay-[100ms]">
        <span class="font-mk-display text-sm text-mk-accent tracking-wider block mb-3">01</span>
        <h2
          class="font-mk-display text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem)] font-normal leading-[1.15] tracking-tight text-mk-text mb-12"
        >
          The idea
        </h2>
        <p class="font-mk-body text-base font-light leading-relaxed text-mk-text-secondary mb-5">
          We kept opening heavy task managers to write down simple things like
          <em class="italic text-mk-text">call the dentist</em> or
          <em class="italic text-mk-text">sketch the garden plan</em>. Those tools were built for
          teams, sprints, and dashboards &mdash; not for a single human trying to hold onto a
          thought until evening.
        </p>
        <p class="font-mk-body text-base font-light leading-relaxed text-mk-text-secondary">
          todo-app is the opposite. No accounts. No sync servers. No notifications buzzing at
          midnight. Just a quiet page that remembers what you wrote this morning.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div
        class="flex items-start justify-center pt-8 animate-mk-fade-in-up duration-[800ms] delay-[300ms]"
      >
        <div
          class="paper-card bg-mk-paper p-8 border border-mk-border-light rounded-[2px] shadow-mk-soft max-w-[340px] relative max-sm:p-6 max-sm:max-w-full"
        >
          <span
            class="font-mk-body text-[0.7rem] uppercase tracking-[0.1em] text-mk-text-muted font-medium block mb-4 pl-5"
          >
            A note to self
          </span>
          <p class="font-mk-body text-[0.95rem] italic leading-relaxed text-mk-text pl-5">
            &ldquo;The best tools are the ones you forget you&rsquo;re using. I want todo-app to
            feel like the back of an envelope &mdash; always within reach, never in the way.&rdquo;
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </SectionInner>
</section>

<style>
  .paper-card::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 2rem;
    bottom: 0;
    width: 1px;
    background: rgba(217, 213, 205, 0.5);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .paper-card::before {
      left: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
